<plot>No words, only visuals, music and human emotions. Obfuscation is a short dramatic film that incorporates no dialogue in its storytelling. Instead the film utilizes cinematic technique, artistic expression, musical tone and acting through sub-text to tell it's tale of love and loss, as we follow the emotional tribulations of a lonely artist, whose sorrow for his lost love drives him to create three paintings of pure emotional expression.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?406381</url></doc>
